data.text: Alex looks really tired today. They came into class, went straight to their desk and put their head down.
"Hey. You're asking if I'm okay?? Kinda not really. I didn't get any sleep last night and I'm worried about how well I can do at today's project. It's stressing me out."
"Thanks for asking though, I appreciate it. I might just take a nap during the break and should be fine after."

blackboardData.blackboardText: Skylar's sitting at their desk and their leg is shaking a lot and staring straight at their desk. How will you get their attention?

jsonData.errorMsg: You said hi but it looks like they didn't hear you. Maybe there is another way to greet them.

data.text: Gray is pacing around the room.
"Oh sorry, didn't see you there. Me? How am I doing? Not okay! I didn't know we had a group project today. I didn't do last night's homework so I don't know the topic too well."
"Maybe I'll read up on it during the break. Thanks for asking!"

jsonData.caption: To get someone's attention, try waving.
